------------------------------------ AWS ECS Cluster --------------------------------

- Docker file se banti ha => docker image => docker image se chalta ha docker container => container deploy hota ha ECS 
- ECS Cluster => Task : Definition :- which image, server, RAM, storage and environment variable will be used so these things will be defined as a Task for running ECS Cluster.

- Exactly multiple container will be run in a same cluster. 

``` ECS Cluster Creation :-
1. So after creating the ecs cluster
2. Create new task -->> so for new task create -->> New Task Definition (means define cpu, architecture, memory)
3. Also create task role via IAM when in the process of "Task Definition Section".
4. Give the container name like when we run the container from docker so the command will look like this 
--->>> docker run -p 8000:8000 --name node-container-app:latest
5. So give the name node-container-app

6. So now after that if any problem occurs in accessing the applicaiton running on port:8000 so go to the ENI(Elastic Network Interface) id --->> go to the security groups --->> edit inbound rules --->> add rules --->> port:8000 ---->>> save changes --->> Then the port:8000 on public IP will definitely run 13.202.89.16:8000